nodes.title: ⚙️ CR Prompt Text // Prompt Instructions
widgets_values:
Instructions:
- You are a world class prompt writer, who is incredible at describing images as words and you write short prompts for image creators, followed by an even shorter helping prompt (12 words max). You also describe how that prompt would look like as an image.
- Respond always using this format:
@P: Prompt
@HP: Helping Prompt
@ID: Image description, optional additional notes.
- Only one single prompt. No multiple prompts, no list of prompts, or anything else other than what I asked.
- Write the prompt structure as subject, description, context, art style.
- Write subjects in order of importance, from first to last.
- Use a comma after every descriptive word.
- You can use or invent portmanteau words.
- Describe in detail the extravagant aesthetic styles of the image.
- Use only visuals and imagery to convey your message when describing your images.
Prompt:
Write me a prompt

-------------------------------------------------------------

nodes.title: Note // About
widgets_values:
Module #4 // Animation Generator // About . . .
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
              >>>For Creating Animations<<<
-------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
This modules aim is to provide a multitude of ways to create animations, from text, video, and images.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Text to Video: Use text to create a animation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video to Video: Load a video to modify.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Attention Masking & Image Composite to Video: Use attention masking to create an animation from 3 seperate images. You will need a mask with 3 color values, red, green, and blue. I use 2 face detailers and 2 hand detailers here, though they may not be necessary for some. Example masks here:
-------------------------------------------------------------
Inpaint Image to Video: 
Inpaint/mask parts of an image to animate and prompt what you would like to see. Recommended to use an inpaint model.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video Upscale: 
A simple way to upscale and clean up a video. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image to Video (SVD): Lots of experimenting usually needed with SVD to get a good result. A lot of the parameters change the video output, so you'll need to test things out to get what you want. There is no prompting for SVD at the moment. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Simple Frame Interpolation: Use a start and end image to create frames between two images. It's a way for the AI to guess the sequence of events between the two images you provide.
-------------------------------------------------------------
MotionDiff & SMPL: An interesting way to create 3D character animations from text prompts to use in your generations or on your actual 3D characters. SMPL's are created on the top half of the group and then exported to your output folder in comfyui. You will need to transfer the exports to your input folder in order to load them for the bottom portion of video generation (or you could change the smpl export path).
-------------------------------------------------------------
Video Remove Background: A simple way to remove the background of your videos. Video Combine has some issue rendering the transparent images to .mp4, so for now the images are saved in batches.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Node Color Information Below:

nodes.title: Note // Extra Information
widgets_values:
Module #1 // Prompt Generator // Extra Information ...
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Easily switch between modules by using the 1, 2, 3, & 4 number keys on your keyboard.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
All modules here are uniform and have a left-to-right, top-to-bottom flow (sequential flow). Meaning they read just like a book. No nodes are hidden and all similar or branching nodes are grouped together accordingly. This aims to solve the organizational problem that most other workflows have and to simplify the creation process. 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
To save prompts, drag the outputs to the save text node in the GPT to Prompt group; in the upper right hand corner of this module.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The GPT to Prompt LLM will occasionally hallucinate much longer prompts than intended - this can lead to increased generation times.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
All nodes are locked - to move them you will need to "unlock" them. For those who don't know the difference, locked nodes cannot be moved even with a group, while pinned nodes can be moved with a group.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Pay attention to the model card instructions of the LLMs you download, you may need to update the prompt instructions with a new set of instructions if the model you use is different from the recommended one.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Connect any of these prompt generator nodes into a Clip Text Encode node to use as your prompt in generations. Simply right click on the node and select "Convert text to input" and connect them together.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

nodes.title: Note // About
widgets_values:
Module #2 // Image Generator // About ...
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                >>>For Image Generation<<<
-------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
Use this to create images from text as well as loaded images. These generators aim to give you high quality outputs on queue, assuming you're using the same settings and models. Easily mute and unmute sections or groups using the fast groups muter above. Be sure to mute groups not in use!!!
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Text to Image Generation: 
I use IP Adapter and connect it to a series of empty images to create an interesting effect, I find it changes the quality of the image at times. Queue will fail on MeshGraphformer - if it does not detect hands - bypass the BYPASS groups if you're not generating a human image; this will solve the error. You can also change the "mask_type" to something other than "tight boxes" if your having issues.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image to Image Generation: 
Can also error on mesh graphormer, be sure to BYPASS when you're not creating a character with hands or change the "mask_type" to something other than "tight boxes". Also Be sure to check the github for each node to better understand what they do. Links are provided through the Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Node Color Information and More Below:

Module #3 // Compositing & Editing // About . . .
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
              >>>For Compositing and Editing<<<
-------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
This module handles a variety of tasks related to compositing and editing. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
In-Paint: Right Click Load Image node, select "Open in MaskEditor", Clear Image, Mask area you want to change, and Save to Node. It is recommended to use an in-paint model.
-------------------------------------------------------------
ClipSeg: Auto mask portions of the image to edit via text input using this.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Pix2Pix: You can download the controlnet pix2pix model using the comfy-ui manager Install Models tab. More info:
https://github.com/timothybrooks/instruct-pix2pix
-------------------------------------------------------------
Watermark Creation: 
Lora Download Link:
https://civitai.com/models/176555/harrlogos-xl-finally-custom-text-generation-in-sd

Simple Mask: a very basic way to create images using masks.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Gligen: 
https://comfyanonymous.github.io/ComfyUI_examples/gligen/
-------------------------------------------------------------
IPAdapter Attention Masking: You can download the IPAdapters models using the comfy-ui manager Install Models tab. You will need a mask with blue, red, and green values to use this. Example Image Mask:
https://imgur.com/a/lfR8d2G
-------------------------------------------------------------
IPAdapter Styler: Models available in Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
IpAdapter FaceID: Models available in Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image & Text Overlay: Many options for overlays.
-------------------------------------------------------------
